-- Harlequins Defeat Sale to Claim Top Spot in Rugby’s Premiership
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-05-05T15:35:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-05/harlequins-defeat-sale-to-claim-top-spot-in-rugby-s-premiership.html
Harlequins beat Sale Sharks 24-10 to
clinch first place in English rugby’s Premiership and the top
spot in the playoffs.  Danny Care and Mike Brown scored tries and Nick Evans
kicked 14 points as Harlequins finished with 75 points, one more
than Leicester Tigers, which beat Bath 28-3, and two ahead of
Saracens, a 40-22 winner over Exeter Chiefs.  Harlequins will host fourth-place  Northampton Saints  in the
opening semifinal on May 12, with Saracens visiting Leicester
later that day. The winners advance to the Premiership final May
26 at Twickenham Stadium in  London .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
